17/10/2008
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Police said on Thursday (October 16th) they detained six people allegedly involved in an arms-smuggling ring that includes several EU countries.
Officers arrested the six on Wednesday and Thursday in Sarajevo and three other central towns:
Travnik, Vitez and Zenica.
State Investigation and Protection Agency chief Dragan Lukac said police seized a large stash of weapons and ammunition during searches in eight locations across the country.
(Fena, AFP - 16/10/08)
